dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation. Division of Forestry, Geology, Parks, and Historic Sites. Atlas Sheet 35 (1946) New Jersey Geological Survey. Alternate title: [New Jersey.] Atlas sheet no. 35. Relief show by 10 ft. (5 ft in southwester part). contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by soundiings in feet at low tide.Title was not given. Region covered: vicinity of Millville. Original survey made under direction of C. C. Vemeule, Topographer, in 1886. 1946 revision by R. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1946.
